<scriptment id="96000" point="woeful_inadequacy" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-11-22" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>Yuki looks down on the former Cardboard City.<comment>The City always goes down, even without the conditions met in Scene 89000.</comment></narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Every day spreads thinner the resources we require.</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Those economic, those romantic, those spiritual.</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Eventually we will all encounter some impassable obstacle in our interests.</line>
		<line id="4000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Men in Transition will be stuck in transition, for others own his needs.</line>
		<line id="5000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Our world will become too small for us and our deficits will consume us,</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Because we have programmed ourselves for compromise.</line>
		<line id="7000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">The so-called a priori belief that prowess in the one is deficit in the other.</line>
		<line id="8000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">To bring one up and another down is to never rise.</line>
		<line id="9000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Such Inadequacy is Woeful.</line>
	</part>
</scriptment>